%N A395440 Squares visited by four knights, all starting on square 1, when moving on a square-spiral numbered board and always moving to the lowest available unvisited square.
%C A395440 All four knights, numbered 1..4, start at square one, and each moves in turn to the lowest available unvisited square, starting with the lowest numbered knight.
%C A395440 The sequence is finite - knight 2 is trapped on square 1739 after visiting 477 squares, knight 3 is trapped on square 3850 after visiting 1378 squares, knight 1 is trapped on square 9876 after visiting 3982 squares, and knight 4 is trapped on square 12041 after visiting 4735 squares, giving a total of 10569 visited squares.
%H A395440 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395440/b395440.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10569</a>
%H A395440 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395440/a395440_1.png">Image of the knights' paths</a>. The knights' paths are colored red, yellow, green and blue, the final squares for knights 1, 2 and 3 are colored yellow, and the final square for knight 4 is colored red.
%Y A395440 Cf. A338290, A395439, A395441-A395444, A316667.
